    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Hey @samczsun thanks but I'm not sure this should be a concern (at least not anymore).\r\n\r\nIf `SendHTTPRequest` returns an error, mev-boost won't crash (DoS) it will just log the error.\r\n\r\nFor example, when requesting headers (bids) from each relay:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/flashbots/mev-boost/blob/7713bd9445dc817d75c506b63397662a792d1270/server/service.go#L328-L333\r\n\r\nAdditionally, these types have been fuzzed quite a bit. See this file:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/flashbots/go-boost-utils/blob/main/types/builder_fuzz_test.go\r\n\r\nHow does this look to you?",
